id: pm-v68d
title: Add pm_schema and pm_config narrow MCP tools for workspace configuration via MCP
description: "pm schema (add-type/remove-type/add-status/remove-status/list/show) and pm config (get/set/unset) are both fully wired in runAction switch cases but have no narrow tools — agents must use pm_run. These are primary workspace-configuration operations agents perform during project setup (e.g. adding a Story type, setting default status, enabling telemetry). Narrow pm_schema and pm_config tools would surface required args (subcommand, key/name) at top-level with proper descriptions, participate in the unexpected-key warning system, and be self-documenting. pm_schema already has a subcommand enum in pm_run's schema — that schema should migrate to a dedicated tool."
type: Feature
status: open
priority: 3
tags[3]: agent-ux,"area:mcp",dx
